India Wins Toss, Bats Against Pakistan in Semifinal at Cricket World Cup

-- B y   C h r i s   E l s e r
-- 
2011-03-30T08:48:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-30/india-wins-toss-will-bat-against-pakistan-in-cricket-world-cup-semifinal.html
India  will bat first in its Cricket
World Cup semifinal match against  Pakistan  after winning the
coin toss.  The winner will play  Sri Lanka , which defeated  New Zealand 
in the other semifinal yesterday, in the April 2 final.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Chris Elser at 
 celser@bloomberg.net  